    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="1646"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1646">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 511.4A1/1470.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2494.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the Netherlands</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 22, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: Referring to my note No. 2424
                    of the 12th instant, by which I took leave to announce to your excellency that
                    the Opium Conference would open on June 15 next, I have the honor to inform you
                    that it appears from a communication which I have just received from my
                    Government that the Austro-Hungarian Government which for formal reasons has not
                    yet been able to sign the Convention has declared its adhesion to the contents
                    of the Convention and its readiness to enforce its provisions if the other
                    Governments decide that the Convention may be put into operation.</p>
                <p>Be pleased to accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. L. F. C. de Rappard</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
